Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.12,0:01:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They've got all kinds of big people in the world now.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.88,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People were smaller when I first got here.\NNow they're all bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.90,0:01:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you doing, Dr. Robinson?\NGood to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we say hi to people here, over here?\NThere.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.38,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, sweetheart.\NDid we miss anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.62,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we miss anybody?\NThe ladies wanted to say hi to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.41,0:01:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sweetheart, yeah, hi.\NWe'll come up to this side and go around.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NNow we'll go do more things.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.35,0:01:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\NGood to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.59,0:01:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Sherry, my son's wife.\NHello.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NNice to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.52,0:02:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes.\NHi, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?\NGood to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.19,0:02:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I got you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.50,0:02:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, we've got to do this side again now.\NThis is by Lindahl from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, I remember now, yeah.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, say I love you.\NAh, here's all the people here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, hi.\NGood to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:02:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NIt's an honor to be with you again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.02,0:03:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Doc.\NI'm so happy to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.88,0:03:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.12,0:03:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody we miss, we don't want to miss anybody, huh?\NWe want everybody to get to heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to miss anybody, huh?\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.05,0:03:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Get there and say, where's George?\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't say hello to everybody, we have to back up the bus.\NGo back and pick up George.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.24,0:03:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's got 20 more years to go.\NHoly God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We get everybody?\NThen we get everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.32,0:03:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We're better.\NRight on time, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.23,0:03:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right on time.\NIt's turned on, so I can hear what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.94,0:04:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's in the side control room today?\NGabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Gabe.\NLet's see how he works.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.94,0:04:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see you do that, eh?\NOh, the egos dream to be in control.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.73,0:04:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To rule everybody.\NMake them do what you want them to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.55,0:04:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Make them think what you want them to think.\NBehave the way you want them to behave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.60,0:04:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And die for you, too.\NJust a minor thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.78,0:05:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You should die for my beliefs.\NThat's today's rule internationally.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.62,0:05:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You all should die because of what I think.\NOkay, so we start out the lecture with the ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That saves listening to the whole thing.\NYou can go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.66,0:05:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We start from the beginning.\NAnd we'll talk about leaving anything after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My final piece of advice is the way to the ultimate truth\Nis really to become the context instead of the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.04,0:05:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To make one's life a prayer.\NTo become that which people talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.38,0:05:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To be kindly.\NTo be forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:06:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To see and witness the sacredness of all things.\NAnd if you stay with the context continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.45,0:06:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually what you witness\Nis that everything comes about spontaneously,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.39,0:06:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,all on its own everything happens automatically is a consequence of the very nature of reality\Nitself there is no personal you doing anything all that's happening of its own all you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,do is reject the vanity that there is an eye causing all that to happen the willingness to\Nlet go seeing yourself as cause all happens spontaneously so with humility you say to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.87,0:07:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,mind you don't you see what's happening but you don't understand it you don't understand it all\Nyou can provide is an explanation and an explanation is not the reality the explanation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.18,0:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is extraneous to the reality it has to be in order to be an explanation\Nhmm
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so with sort of a deep humility you begin to witness that everything is happening spontaneously\Nof its own because there is potentiality potentiality then manifests as an actuality
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:08:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does so by the power of the field not by the power of you minor little correction\Nmakes the difference between heaven and hell
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.60,0:08:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,well\Nminor
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.96,0:08:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd argue meant and all kinds of things all right so don't go with the ego and don't listen to\Nreason because that's its playground it plays with your head don't let it play with your head
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.15,0:09:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,say I don't want to go there it's a matter of witnessing we said there's two main spiritual\Npractices meditation and contemplation meditation serves its purposes at specific times in your life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.59,0:09:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,where you have a mind you're not listening to the narrative right now there are two forms of the self\Nyou can't live there
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.43,0:09:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,because you won't cross the first street\Nha ha ha ha
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,together in laden\Nyou can get taken out by the bus you know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.87,0:09:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,ha\Nall right so meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we're just finishing a book nowhere finishing two books simultaneously as we knock off the tail of the last one three\Nbooks
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nin one of the books anyway
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:09:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,ha ha ha ha\NIt has to do with meditation and contemplation as a specific subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation has its place.\NIt's very specific. It's very focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.66,0:10:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It always talks about one-pointedness of mind.\NBut it leads in, to me, meditation can also become a diversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.92,0:10:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many are the meditators. Few are the enlightened.\NAnd there's reasons for it, which we do cover in the lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.65,0:10:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because meditation is somewhat removed from life.\NFor 20 years or something, I did it for an hour in the morning and an hour in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.48,0:10:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your life gets busy, then you begin to skip it.\NYou take a class on meditation, you do a workshop, and boy, you're enthusiastic as all get-out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.53,0:10:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, for maybe four or six months.\NAnd then your aunt Tilly gets sick and visits, and well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.51,0:11:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you abandon it.\NYou abandon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not who you are.\NIt's something you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.08,0:11:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it gets, it becomes held dualistically.\NThere's a me that's meditating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A me here and now that's meditating then and there.\NSo it's not really you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.66,0:11:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often, I think, there's deviations that are labeled meditation,\Nbut they're really methods of achieving altered states of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.11,0:11:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you stop whatever the thing is you're doing,\Nthe altered state of consciousness disappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.63,0:11:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the states that arise in sort of, to me, artificially-induced states are transitory.\NThey're called satori.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They come and they go.\NAnd you can stand up and walk around and open your eyes to the spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Transitory.\NThey are useful in another way because they give you a glimpse that there is another dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.69,0:12:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,another experiential dimension.\NThere is another experiential dimension there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.29,0:12:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, the difficulty, as we pointed out in the lectures,\Nand we'll probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll cross over it again today,\Nis the idea that one can catch the space between two thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.53,0:12:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any space between two thoughts, folks.\NAnd nobody's ever found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.57,0:12:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll clarify that.\NIt's the space prior to the thoughts out of which all thoughts arise, a common field.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So contemplation then is a lifestyle, a way of being in the world.\NAnd first, it's a disciplined practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, that's the reality of who you have become.\NThere is no this and that because you are that to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So that state, that condition that you contemplate,\Nthe reason it works is because it is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that funny?\NYou imitate your real self artificially.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.87,0:13:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, everything's beautiful.\NYes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to say everything's beautiful.\NBut that's a steam engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.53,0:13:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that beautiful?\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.95,0:13:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm supposed to see its beauty.\NSo you stand back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.18,0:13:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the horse apples on the street?\NAre they beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.17,0:13:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother was Wisconsin, Milwaukee.\NYou know, when I grew up, horse and wagons were prevalent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.32,0:13:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And electric cars, gimbals and all, had electric carts.\NLooked like sort of UPS trucks today, but they're electric.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.74,0:13:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're quiet.\NAnd then there were the horses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.83,0:13:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the streets would get pretty thick.\NWe didn't go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.37,0:14:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The store came by.\NIt came in a wagon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.23,0:14:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,There was the fish man, the meat man, the bakery man, the utensils man, the hardware man.\NEverything came down the alley.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.84,0:14:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So you didn't have to really go to the store.\NBut on a hot, hot day after a rain, it got pretty strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.20,0:14:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And my granddad, he said, you know what?\NI'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.\NI'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.28,0:14:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.\NI'm going to go to the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go to the store.\NAnd my grandmother, you know, would call up the sanitation department.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.88,0:14:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And she'd say, it's so strong, it's making the tears come to my eyes.\NAnd then you'd see the guys down there, four breasts, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.89,0:14:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a different way of life, huh?\NJust a different way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, when you're broke, that's a good job sweeping up that stuff.\NI would have taken it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too small.\NYou got to be stronger, they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NThose big brims are very heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd think they're light.\NNo, they're pretty heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.21,0:15:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,After three hours, they really get heavy.\NAll of that is apropos of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And why not?\NEverything is apropos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.24,0:15:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Something has gotten us into a hell of a pickle.\NI think it's best to concentrate on things that are totally unimportant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.21,0:15:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I was concentrating on something absolutely, totally unimportant.\NSomething I got.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, incredible discovery.\NSee how it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.26,0:15:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'd been thinking about something important, I would have never realized it.\NI don't know whether to tell them or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.\NShould we tell them what the realization was?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.13,0:15:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NAbsolutely?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.13,0:15:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know it myself.\NWhat was the purpose of this life, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This life was very strange in many ways.\NYou know, starting at age three, I was thinking about life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.32,0:16:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about my family.\NI was thinking about my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was thinking about myself.\NYou know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about my family.\Nand then recurrently at age 12, and periodically, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.24,0:16:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, you know, at least from a historical viewpoint,\Nrather unusual in the staggering states.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.02,0:16:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thought was, how come?\NAnd then one time I was giving a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.74,0:16:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was here someplace, you know, the other hotel, I think.\NAnd I'm walking down the aisle, and I could leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.12,0:16:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know whether I was going to leave or not.\NThe permission to leave, which has been recurrent also.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.47,0:16:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But no, the body continued to walk on.\NAnd I thought it looked sort of funny it falling down in the middle of a lecture,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.43,0:16:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's none of my business, so it walked on.\NI said, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.43,0:17:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems to be like some kind of a commitment.\NSo thinking about nothing at all this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with manuscripts of various books around,\Nit seems that the purpose is to give witness and to testify
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.31,0:17:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to the reality of divinity as the source of one's experience,\Nto testify and give witness to the subjective experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,which is of such an incredible nature that it cannot adequately be described.\NIt emanates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.54,0:17:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It emanates of its own energy.\NTo give witness to that reality, which is done periodically throughout history,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in various cultures.\NAnd then it becomes mystified over time and given authoritative,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and develops into some kind of a religion.\NAnd that brings me to the crashing halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.45,0:18:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And simultaneously, to develop a scientific objective means of discerning that truth.\NFirst of all, then, the obligation is to witness the inner experience of the revelation of truth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of reality.\NAnd when you do that, you're going to be able to see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be able to see the truth.\NYou're going to be able to see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.03,0:18:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be able to see one's existence.\NThen to, like, go outside of yourself, the person of that state,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.78,0:18:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and develop a science of consciousness,\Nwhich we did as the calendar of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And to first be that, witness it.\NBecause to speak of it with any energy of truth is to spread the energy forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.74,0:18:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThen, because it happened to somebody who also, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.06,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was a scientist, physician, psychiatrist, psychoanalyst,\Nthe capacity to then go outside the state
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and describe it in terminology comprehensible to the world\Nin the 400s, in the intellectual, logical.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.00,0:19:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's one thing to experience it.\NIt's quite another to describe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So this gave a yardstick,\Nan objective means of discerning truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So first to experience the truth,\Nwitness its validity,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to testify to it as a reality,\Nand then to share with the world
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.99,0:19:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the means of discerning truth from falsehood,\Nwhich the world has never had to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This world has never had any means\Nof discerning truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:20:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The best that has arisen is the inner state of the mystic,\Nbut that's incomprehensible to probably 99.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.44,0:20:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of the world, you know.\NNot too pragmatically valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.55,0:20:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, you see, first to be it,\Nthen to describe how it can be described
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.72,0:20:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is verifiable by the world,\Nand thereby transcend Descartes' duality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.24,0:20:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of res interna and res externa.\NTake that, Rene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.04,0:20:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We got them by both, you know what.\NComing and going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.58,0:20:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna.\NThe mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.27,0:20:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our society doesn't understand mystic at all,\Nbut I'm going to try to give it a few sentences
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:21:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book I'm doing now.\NThe mystic, that's the inner experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.11,0:21:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of the self.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.77,0:21:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna.\NOne's inner subjective state.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.28,0:21:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there is res externa.\NWhat's out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.27,0:21:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The world of nature.\NIt's creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.69,0:21:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's...\NThere's creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and what creation actually is.\NThen there's what the mind thinks about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is totally screwed up,\Nbut useful, thankfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, you wouldn't be able to get on an airplane\Nand one end and get off at the other, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.55,0:21:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Pragmatically useful.\NAnyway, having just discovered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.37,0:21:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd share it.\NNever did in a while I was here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but I got it this morning.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.26,0:21:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Zappo.\NLook out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.46,0:22:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's see.\NWhere's the pointer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.20,0:22:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need the pointer.\NNow, most of the people here have...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.48,0:22:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you, sir.\N...have been here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.70,0:22:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How many new people do we have?\NOh, my gracious me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.30,0:22:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here hasn't read Power vs. Force?\NGet his number.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.40,0:22:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Get his number.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.10,0:22:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so a rapid review then.\NWe try to go over that which we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.60,0:22:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,have shared already,\Nbecause no matter how many times you go over it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.57,0:22:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you get something new,\Njust like I did this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.01,0:22:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we want to cover what we have presented before,\Nbecause from the academic viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.23,0:22:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, as a professor, et cetera.\NSo from an academic viewpoint,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.34,0:22:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we do want to make sure that the material is covered.\NA lot of the material in and of itself is transformative.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.92,0:23:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to have heard that and go,\Noh, wow, you're somewhat different than you were before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.40,0:23:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard it, you know.\NSo we want to share it for didactic responsibility to the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.16,0:23:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I respect the intellect,\Nit has certainly served mankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.66,0:23:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly in the form of science.\NIf it wasn't for the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.96,0:23:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,most of us probably wouldn't be here.\NWe would have died early on of typhoid, diphtheria, syphilis,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.48,0:23:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,tuberculosis, polio, all the things.\NWhen I started out in medicine,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.53,0:23:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was the head of the infectious disease hospital,\Npeople died right and left of all those things,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.71,0:23:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,typhoid and diphtheria and whooping cough and scarlet fever\Nand meningitis.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.01,0:23:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, due to science and logic and reason,\Nwe're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.44,0:24:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's only a fool that belittles the intellect.\NWe'll get around to the difficulties of relativistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.75,0:24:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get around to the distorted hermeneutics\Nof relativism later.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.11,0:24:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The beast.\NThe beast of relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.86,0:24:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to snatch the innocence of humans.\NBut I've declared war on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.75,0:24:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The way I declare war is I put a magnifying glass on it\Nand then the problem just shoots out at you and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.10,0:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NAll right, so we've got this map of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.14,0:24:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's...\NIt was because we discovered how to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.02,0:24:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the purpose of this life as well.\NMankind never had such a means.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.38,0:25:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was discovered via kinesiology\Nthat kinesiology was not as presumed a cause and effect
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.23,0:25:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,local phenomena.\NOn the contrary, the response was due to comparing a stimulus
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.99,0:25:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,with the absolute.\NAnd that the fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.09,0:25:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness itself,\Nwhich is like a giant electrostatic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.20,0:25:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't do anything.\NAnd yet when a stimulus is provided,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.40,0:25:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it responds in an equal and opposite clarity,\Nmuch like an electrostatic,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.02,0:25:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what you would call the old electrostatic speaker system.\NSo what happens then?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.07,0:25:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the presence of truth,\Nthe energy goes out through the acupuncture system,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.81,0:25:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the body is strong.\NThe protoplasm recognizes that which is supportive of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.22,0:26:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is positive and that which is true.\NWhen it's absent, it goes weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.02,0:26:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the test is not true versus false.\NThe test is true versus not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.43,0:26:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That which has no reality.\NIf you're an electrostatic fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.43,0:26:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,then you only respond to the charge of that which is real.\NIf a fake truth is presented to you, you don't react,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.94,0:26:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because it doesn't have any reality to it.\NThere's no reality, no energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.72,0:26:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't really exist in the realm.\NIt's only a proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.26,0:26:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a proposition, but it's not an actuality.\NWhen you're presented with a loving mother
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.26,0:26:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,taking care of her children,\Nher energy as she makes noodle soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.26,0:26:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got a different phenomena.\NIt goes up to 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.52,0:26:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma yoga, the sacrifice,\None's convenience for the welfare,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.06,0:26:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the survival and happiness of others,\Nis the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.06,0:27:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's karma yoga.\NWe then ended up with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.25,0:27:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I've been a psychiatrist\Nand through Columbia Psychoanalytic.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.25,0:27:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the so-called emergency emotions down here.\NThese are what we've classified as the welfare emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.44,0:27:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been classically aligned this way\Nas the perennial philosophy for many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.44,0:27:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You could give us the author of this scale,\Nabout 10 or 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.44,0:27:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,different authors.\NWe found it's a very practical,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.44,0:27:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,very practical,\Nwith a little expertise.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.20,0:27:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology only works if you're aligned with knowing the truth.\NThis is, in the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.76,0:27:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can ask a question,\Nin the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.76,0:27:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ego is subtle\Nand it's always trying to proposition some gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.76,0:28:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,some gain, some gain, some gain.\NPersonal questions are likely to be often
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.84,0:28:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the motivation.\NTherefore, you have to have the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.18,0:28:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detached, detached,\Nscientifically, clinically detached.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.18,0:28:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to do it is to ask the question,\Nin the name of the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.18,0:28:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get a book in the mail.\NSusan, I'll do it, I'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.98,0:28:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the name of the highest good,\Nit's well for me to read this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.98,0:28:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,.\N.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.98,0:28:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a lot of no's.\NWe get a lot of yeses, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.46,0:28:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So I don't want to have a position about it.\NI don't want to be impressed by the name of the author.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.46,0:28:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be impressed by the color of the book.\NI just want to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.46,0:28:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest truth,\Nwhat does this calibrate at.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.00,0:29:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dedication is through the truth.\NSo anybody can recapitulate the scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.00,0:29:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody can choose their own numbers.\NYou don't have to use these numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, clinically,\Nclinically a lot of people use one to ten you know on a level of one to ten
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.66,0:29:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,how bad is this headache okay we'll go on to the next so transcending these\Nlevels of consciousness is a manuscript I just finished I just took each level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.15,0:29:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried to show how to escape because there's two traps on each level one is\Nthe gain and the other is the fear of you let go of that gain so that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.44,0:29:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,last slide of today if we're still awake we'll get to it we haven't disappeared\Ninto the these are the enlightened states well the other yeah the other
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.84,0:30:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,scale goes up to 600 because it's extremely rare to go over 600 extremely\Nrare one in 10 million something like that and when it happens 50% of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.97,0:30:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the entity leaves the world\Nthat'd be hard to explain except that is very tempting yeah they say the bliss is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.19,0:30:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total unto itself and the condition of the body is irrelevant so\Nsomething or someone may come along and look after the body or may not or some
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.84,0:30:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulus may come from someplace but it takes a lot to get it moving again so 50\Npercent of the time the people leave you remember from the story of Ruth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.99,0:30:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharshi, he went into that state as a teenager, I forget how old he was, from\Njust an ordinary religious person, he suddenly felt himself dying, so therefore it was an
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.90,0:30:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,actual state.\NPeople talk about going into happy dream states, yeah right, when you feel yourself dying you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.14,0:31:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,know you're about to get there, so he felt himself dying and didn't know if he had or\Nnot, and he came anyway, he went into enlightened state and didn't speak for two years, he was
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.48,0:31:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,by himself and when he was discovered he was covered with mosquito, animal bites, insect\Nbites and he hadn't eaten, and by entreaty he resumed the physicality, but it was two
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.64,0:31:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,years before he spoke again, and the condition that was experienced in this lifetime was\Nnever spoken about for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.75,0:31:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It took 30 years to ever even refer to it, and even to refer to it now, it's the state\Nand you have to stop talking, so we won't talk about it, start talking about that, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.01,0:32:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,gets their money back, no, no, all right, so 600 is a state of satananda, a state of\Nbliss, it's self-fulfilling, whether physicality continues after that is frankly totally different
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.49,0:32:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,from what it used to be, it's totally irrelevant, it is absolutely irrelevant, so there must\Nbe some reason for it, and if there is a reason for it, it gets up and walks around again
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.39,0:32:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually resumes life, my god, all those years I never knew until this morning, it\Nwalked around for no reason, for reasons only, you know, you could hypothecate, it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.70,0:32:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,really until this morning I suddenly realized why I kept walking around, why I didn't fall\Nover, right, and the luxury, I mean, I didn't know, I was down that end and I didn't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.32,0:32:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed to walk right on again, I said, well, that's it, you know, all right, so\Nthis is the state of enlightenment, the state of enlightenment is reached by women and men,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:33:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,men and women, it is not a sexist proposition, god doesn't have genitals, and the denotation\Nhe is, is only a semantic convenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.09,0:33:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Divinity is beyond gender, the non-linear is beyond gender, so, you know, you can't\Npolitically sexualize religion, which sometimes comes up in the question and answer period
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.12,0:33:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in various parts of the country, you know, I'm a sexist because God's called he, you\Nhave to ask God about it, don't ask me about it, I don't know, it's a quality, it's a presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.83,0:33:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it's so far beyond gender that it's comical when they come up with a question, all right,\Nso beyond 600 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.39,0:34:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond 600, there is no such thing as a linear reality, and gender, of course, is comical,\Nso here you realize you are, now this is an interesting thing, which we'll get to later,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.85,0:34:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,also a recent discovery, also a recent discovery, below 200 entities, whether they're human\Nor animal, experience, experience, experience the phenomenon of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.80,0:34:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.00,0:34:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.16,0:34:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.34,0:34:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.40,0:34:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.48,0:34:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, there is the experience of experience, experiencing of life, but they don't realize\Nthey are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.94,0:34:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only at 200, you realize you are.\NSo I was writing about it this week and somebody got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.14,0:35:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I use this analogy, you say to the kitty, what is it like to be a cat?\NThe cat says.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.59,0:35:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean, cat?\NOh, you're a dumb cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.37,0:35:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what you are.\NYou are a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.24,0:35:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what that means.\NWhat does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.50,0:35:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I'll get the encyclopedia.\NI get the encyclopedia, and I get cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.72,0:35:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, we opened it to cat.\NThe cat sits there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.74,0:35:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, listen carefully.\NI put on my glasses, and I read the whole thing about cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.96,0:35:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, now do you understand what it is to be a cat?\NI can't make any sense out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.81,0:35:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I say, well, the cat, damn it, then who are you?\NThe cat says, I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.87,0:36:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The cat realizes that it exists.\NOverconsciousness level 200 is the awareness of your own existence that you are, that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.72,0:36:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of beingness existence is not present below 200.\NThat's why people below 200 don't care if they kill others,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.38,0:36:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because they don't experience existence,\Nso they don't see that they're destroying your capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.42,0:36:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's two different worlds.\NWe'll see it in the evolution of consciousness and its expression,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.77,0:36:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as the evolution of the animal kingdom.\NYou see that dramatic change at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.95,0:36:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the dinosaur, the rapacious, the killer.\NBelow 200 is the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.85,0:37:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 in the human domain is the killer.\NThe farther down you get, the more serious the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.76,0:37:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then at 200, which is the level of truth,\Nspiritual energy begins to flow, and you realize that you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.08,0:37:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the value of human life shoots up.\NPeople below 200 don't know what it means to exist that I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.19,0:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, they have no awareness\Nthat they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.54,0:37:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They are killing that quality if they kill you.\NAbove 200, you have the beginning of morality, ethics,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.77,0:37:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and because the other, now the value of the other becomes important.\NAnd you see that major transition in humankind,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.61,0:37:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in behavior, and in the animal kingdom.\NAt 200, the killer suddenly becomes the herbivore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.23,0:38:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200, you see the emergence of the elk, the deer,\Nthat which is benign.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.33,0:38:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the development of consciousness onward into the 200s.\NAnd our pets are in the 200s, but the pets are unique,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.44,0:38:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I've never finished the research on that.\NIt's a whole project in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.99,0:38:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why an animal in the 200s, as a species, is capable of experiencing\Nand responding to and recognizing love, which is in the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.13,0:38:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the heart, the heart of the cat\Nand the dog is capable of responding to the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.51,0:38:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's wagging tail is 500, and the cat's purr is 500.\NThe minute the cat experiences the presence of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.30,0:38:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it starts to purr, hmm?\NSafety, security, and love, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.34,0:39:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So how does this little animal, as a species, only about 250,\Nrecognize that quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.29,0:39:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NYeah, so that's a whole research thing in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.88,0:39:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we don't want to get stalled out here, but see,\Nthese are the divine states that one can speak
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.91,0:39:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of as the experiential subjective witness.\NAnd the energy of that statement is forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.88,0:39:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the collective consciousness of all mankind,\Nto be it and then share it raises the level of the sea, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.24,0:39:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So.\NBut people blow things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.02,0:39:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People blow things up.\NPeople blow things up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.96,0:39:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, that's not a reality, is it?\NSubjective reality is not knowable below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:40:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So for 85% of the people on the planet, this is not a knowable reality, huh?\NFor a considerable percentage of the rest, it's an intellectual belief system.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.48,0:40:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They read that so-and-so said that, that, that, and that, that,\Nand therefore they respect it via the intellect, hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.83,0:40:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's 85% of the world we see.\NIt doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.32,0:40:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't experience that they are.\NWow. So we realize the importance of within the ego, a structure called the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.68,0:40:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And that experiencer is like a screen in which all these ego phenomena go on.\NAnd it's one ten-thousandth of a second in advance of the experiencing of subjective reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.00,0:40:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So in meditation, classically, the misinterpretation\Nof the subject is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.10,0:41:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the teaching of the Buddha, which I've spoken to him about, as I told you.\NAnd he agreed, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.26,0:41:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's screwed up.\NThey figured it, fixed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.83,0:41:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The infinite reality is not between two thoughts, it's prior.\NIt's the infinite ocean, silent out, non-linear, out of which the linear arises, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.99,0:41:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. As a consequence of the desire to think and the pleasure of thinking this.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.55,0:41:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's the way the world is balanced.\NThat's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.33,0:41:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's just another way of depicting it.\NPeople say, well, isn't this negativity why we have tsunamis and floods and, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.95,0:41:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That's so dumb.\NI mean, it really is dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.04,0:42:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the end times aren't here, folks.\NThese phenomena went on for millennia before mankind ever got here, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.72,0:42:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And when lightning strikes, saint and sinner alike drown.\NSaint and sinner go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.72,0:42:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Saint and sinner get out in the same ship at the same time.\NAnd all those phenomena went on long before mankind was even thought of.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.22,0:42:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no homo sapien here at all.\NThe dinosaur kingdom was wiped out, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.31,0:42:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Meteors hit the earth and blackened the sky.\NAnd many life forms disappeared, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the dinosaur era, hmm.\NNo. So I don't believe in end times and prophecies and a lot, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.18,0:42:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Oh.\NThis is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.53,0:42:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the evolution of consciousness.\NHow is life going now?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.17,0:42:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was pretty poor for a long time, wasn't it?\NLife wasn't too cool at the time of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.16,0:43:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to have fast-running shoes to survive.\NThen recently, recently, recently, 600,000 years ago is very recent.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.78,0:43:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And new evidence, the redating of the fossil, of the skull, is now projected.\NThe emergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.81,0:43:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The emergence of homo sapien, even earlier than was previously thought.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.59,0:43:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is only a few seconds ago.\NAh. And now, as you can see from the scale, the scale went like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.43,0:43:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the consciousness level of mankind is rising suddenly.\NOkay, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.03,0:43:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.\NAnd that is not going to bring peace, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.73,0:44:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth.\NThe sword of truth is somewhat different than peace, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.04,0:44:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People kill each other over truth, you know.\NTherefore, this rise of consciousness here is going to precipitate very severe conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.07,0:44:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,just by confrontation.\NThat which is false is threatened by that which is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.86,0:44:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Does not look at it favorably.\NDecides it better blow it up and kill it before truth gets loose on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.18,0:44:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and brings their days to an end.\NTherefore, didn't Jesus say that I bring you now the sword of peace or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.58,0:44:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he say?\NWho knows that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.94,0:44:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody?\NAny Christians here?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.96,0:44:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I put their hand up.\NWhat did Christ say about the sword of truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.96,0:44:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know it?\NWhat did he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.46,0:44:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw.\NWell, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.99,0:44:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The sword of truth.\NThe sword of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.54,0:45:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAnd I say, the sword of truth is not necessarily going to bring you hearts and flowers and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.99,0:45:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,hymns and incense.\NHeh.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.70,0:45:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But either you live by the sword of truth or you die by the sword of death.\NHa.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.70,0:45:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,die by the sword of steel, which is what's happening in today's world. That's\Nthe world conflict now, being threatened by the sword of steel. And what is your
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.55,0:45:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,response? Okay, we go on the next one. So anyway, there we have the evolution of\Nthe animal kingdom and the emergence of life over great expanses of time. And it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.05,0:45:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,took like forever for consciousness ever to even get up to 200. As you can see,\Nthese are archeologic ages. We'll move on to the next slide. And here's the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.38,0:46:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom. And here you see these all, these all lived by predation. Therefore, the\Nego, as life interacted with material matter, it evolved, you know, as the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.41,0:46:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness rather, the light of God interacted with physicality. Out of it\Narose the capacity for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.80,0:46:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Life to survive the way it was, the way it originated. Back here, all these people,\Nnone of them have within themself a source of energy. They're all born without batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.82,0:46:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They need a couple of double A's. You just open the box, there's double A batteries\Nin the box. But if the batteries run out, they don't have energy. They don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.05,0:47:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,energy.\NSo how are you going to get energy? You got to get. To survive, you got to get. There
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.69,0:47:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you got the solar plexus fix of the ego for eons of time, and it still operates as the\Nbasis of the animal instincts in the human. All the calibrated levels below 200 are evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.55,0:47:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of the persistence of the instinctual drives of the animal, which were necessary for survival.\NThat's why we can't hate ego, because he has to eat. If he was green, we could sit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.44,0:48:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,him in the sun, and his chlorophyll would re-energize his batteries. But he has no means\Nto re-energize his batteries. He has to eat. That means he has to eat something, or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.01,0:48:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Eat off your thumb, or God knows what it'll do.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.47,0:48:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is, you see the nature here. Then at 200, you see the major shift. And we then\Nhave the animal kingdoms that we love. We love the gorillas. We love the gorillas. I
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.02,0:48:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mean, all normal people love gorillas. They're adorable. And all these animals here, we learn\Nto love them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.60,0:49:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\N. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.12,0:49:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Held the baby, then realized the mother would be afraid of her, laid the baby down.\NYou're the gateway for the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.24,0:49:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it was, like, incredible.\NOkay, next.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.90,0:49:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's over 200.\NWe mentioned today Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.45,0:49:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?\NThere he is, Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.34,0:49:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 470, wow.\NSo people who had a really big impact, intellectually at least, in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.96,0:49:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,were Descartes, Socrates, and Hegel.\NHegel, we'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.41,0:50:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hegel defined, you know, he was a major philosopher in the first half of the 18th century in Germany.\NOne of his principles that calibrates extremely high is the principle of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.22,0:50:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, calibrating levels of truth is calibrating like a thermometer.\NWhat is?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.38,0:50:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the truth of this proposition, entity, or whatever, as compared to the absolute, as compared to the absolute.\NSo the recognition of the reality of the absolute as the primary yardstick of truth, then, was Hegel's contribution.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.57,0:50:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Hegel, at 470, had the intellectual capacity to recognize truth\Nand give it the respect that was due.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.56,0:51:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, as we've said before in previous lectures, Karl Marx's, unfortunately, unresolved edible complex\Nled him into a hatred of authority and edible problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.36,0:51:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So he disenfranchised the truth of Hegel and substituted a relativistic proposition,\Nthe downside of which is the duality of perpetrator and victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.14,0:51:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So all relativism...\NRelativism, which contaminates today's societies, is due to the duality of dividing things perceptually
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.35,0:51:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,into perpetrator and victim.\NPerpetrator and victim depends on point of view, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.93,0:51:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, relativism is, truth is just what you think it is.\NYou can vote on truth, yeah, because it's only perception denies the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.03,0:52:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd it is brought about all the contention in present society.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.57,0:52:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you calibrate it, if you calibrate it, you find, you know, that it calibrates\Nextremely low.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.05,0:52:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you understand the ego dynamics of it, you see that the ego gain, you see the\Nego loses, the ego loses when you get up to the mid-400s, because now you've got to go
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.41,0:52:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,along with the world of logic and verifiable reality.\NThe narcissistic ego loses dominion, and therefore wants to see itself as the arbitrator
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.52,0:52:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality, does not want to surrender its presumptive divinity to something higher than\Nitself, not even the level of Hegel, doesn't want to surrender even to 470, much less divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.85,0:52:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or God, much less divinity or God.\NSo the core of the ego, then, is atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.27,0:52:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Atheistic.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.35,0:53:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is God.\NAnd even if it quotes God, it does so for its own reasons and kills you in the name
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.63,0:53:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of God.\NThat way, it gets to still be God and yet pretend not to be pretentious, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.59,0:53:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NVery clever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.59,0:53:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's happened over the centuries, you see.\NThe Protestant Catholics are busy killing each other off in 30-year wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.49,0:53:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And the history of the crown of England, of course, is extremely interesting.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.45,0:53:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We said to be able to know the truth.\NThe other problem is rhetoric and deviations from truth occur because people purposely
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.93,0:53:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,ignore stating the context.\NA thing is true only within a certain context.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In another context, the same statement is false.\NSo one way of twisting people politically is to ignore the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.12,0:53:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore the context.\NIgnore.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.57,0:54:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore.\NIgnore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.14,0:54:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore.\NIgnore.
