Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.58,0:54:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore.\NIgnore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.58,0:54:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignore.\Nyou may get by with just a deck court. If it's a time of war and you pull the same
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.59,0:54:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,stunt, you'll get a major court-martial, major court-martial. To be intoxicated on\Nduty when the war is over, they'll get you a deck court. Try that when you're under
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.73,0:55:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,fire, find yourself in the brig badly. To be intoxicated and have your finger on\Nthe gun, come over here sailor, put them in the brig. Not the same crime if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.17,0:55:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tied up at the wharf and the war is over and you're intoxicated, you get a\Ncourt-martial, 30 days and that's it. So therefore, context and of course the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.76,0:55:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate context to which you're all answerable throughout all of time is the\Ninfinite truth of the field of consciousness itself, in which all
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.30,0:55:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,things are recorded forever. The field of consciousness, which is a radiance of\Nenergy, which emanates forth as the source of light, the light of God, records
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.50,0:55:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,all phenomena forever, beyond time or location. Therefore, the wonderment of\Nkinesiology, the kinesiologic test, calibrated levels of consciousness, is you're not
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.07,0:56:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,limited to the linear domain. You can ask anything about anything anywhere in\Ntime or place.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.79,0:56:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by the Amara.org community\Nthings that mystify the world, we haven't all saw before breakfast. We track Bin Laden
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.28,0:56:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,every day. Where's Bin Laden today? Well, we put him on the map, he's here, there he is.\NYou track anything and anybody that's going on in the world. And then of course, some of
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.10,0:56:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,those things we wrote about in the book, truth versus falsehood, and by the time\Nthe book's published, it's already news, but we knew it long before it was news.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.86,0:56:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, long before it was news. It's useful in things, in the\Npractical world. You can calibrate the level of intention of a given society, and then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.98,0:57:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,you can calibrate its capability in that area. Therefore, you don't have to walk around being\Nblindsided like our country and others have been throughout time. They're always surprised
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.54,0:57:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,by something that is so huge, it's like you're surprised to find an elephant in the living\Nroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.53,0:57:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,500,000 communists north of the Korean War.\N500,000 Chinese communist troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.81,0:57:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were surprised by them.\NWe were surprised by Pearl Harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.30,0:57:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We were surprised by 9-11.\NWe're always like, what are we, walking idiots, imbeciles?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.37,0:57:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was surprised by the bus when it hit me.\NSurprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.20,0:57:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, okay, we'll move on.\NUm, this is just a verbalization of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.69,0:58:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll move on.\NThese are the virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.63,0:58:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We say at 200, the world becomes different.\NExperientially, the way you experience it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.06,0:58:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience your own existence,\Nyou experience that you are, you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.12,0:58:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, other things become more real, too.\NSo these are attitudes that begin to become real at 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.52,0:58:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, fairness is a stupid question.\NYou know how stupid fair and honest he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.20,0:58:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a joke.\NAmericans are blindsided because they're so naive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.02,0:58:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They think, see the egotism?\NEverybody out there must be like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.67,0:58:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not like you at all.\NThey don't think like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.04,0:58:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't believe like you.\NThey don't behave like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.09,0:59:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got nothing in common with them.\NTo screw the customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.89,0:59:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To screw the customer is a point of honor in certain cultures.\NAnd if you don't, you hang your head in shame
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.19,0:59:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and get beaten when you get home.\NThere's no, you're aware of that, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.52,0:59:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And people have been in those cultures.\NTell us, Dr. Kallenbach and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.26,0:59:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, honesty is not even a concept in their,\Nnot even a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.89,0:59:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean?\NWe have no concern about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.14,0:59:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to get the best price\Nand the best deal you can get,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.68,0:59:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,depending on the circumstance.\NEverybody's been to those cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.93,0:59:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He's gotten home with an ancient relic.\NSouth America is good for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.61,0:59:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a lot of cultures.\NGenuine relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.58,0:59:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They take you secretly to a hidden place.\NThey got all, this isn't, they got a whole theater
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.28,0:59:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's worked out and they unveil these things wrapped\Nin velvet and take it out of a safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.81,1:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This, this is from his grandfather.\NIt was given to him by a brave who had an arrow in his chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.19,1:00:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, take this.\NThis is from my grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.61,1:00:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandfather's hand shook.\NHe put it away because he knew it was so priceless.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.62,1:00:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been kept in the family vault three generations.\NBut now, the family is poor.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.32,1:00:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The children are sick and need operations.\NFor $10,000, you can have the small one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.67,1:00:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, there's more of them.\NGreed comes up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.25,1:00:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How about 200,000 for all of them?\NOh, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.20,1:00:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't, me with the family, you hear weeping in there, crying.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.44,1:00:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.68,1:00:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.94,1:00:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.60,1:00:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.76,1:00:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.96,1:00:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.34,1:00:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, no, no, no.\NOh, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.48,1:00:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So help me God.\NOh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.78,1:01:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She gives up the family treasure of three generations.\NWeeping, he comes and tells you, I know you will take good care of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.19,1:01:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll go to the bank with you.\NEverybody here is the chap of the world if that happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.12,1:01:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You find it's a plastic.\NIt was made in China.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.76,1:01:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They make them by the thousands.\NAnd so would have dishonored him in the eyes of the family.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.08,1:01:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NIt's like a reverse culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.39,1:01:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you understand why America doesn't do too good in international diplomacy?\NOK, we'll do the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.46,1:01:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Move to the next.\NThis is what the mind does.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.82,1:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't want to talk about the mind now.\NGo ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.44,1:02:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This, I want to say I'm going to redo the slide, and I never do.\NSo we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.30,1:02:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the functions of the mind.\NYou can see why it is sort of an endless trap, because once you get caught in it, it's pretty
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.48,1:02:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,hard to get out.\NWhat are we doing on time?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.04,1:02:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what's going on in the world.\N1115, we take a break?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.34,1:02:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.\NYou know how long it takes to get enlightened?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.24,1:02:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it takes 50 years to recover from it.\NI would say, if you're serious about spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.76,1:03:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that this is not a game, not an intellectual game.\NOnce you start pulling in the power of divinity by supplication, by declaration, I surrender
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.79,1:03:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,my life to thee, oh Lord.\NI pray to be thy servant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.66,1:03:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.66,1:03:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You just did something.\NLife ain't the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.86,1:03:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The consequences are different.\NThe sequence of options that comes up is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.02,1:03:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You just put a different program on your set.\NWhen you do that, always be aware that you may have to make as a consequence some adjustment
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.18,1:03:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,later in life.\NYeah, you may.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.49,1:03:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, how do you want things handled?\NPeople think, isn't that presumptuous?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.91,1:04:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not presumptuous, because it's more or less like taking down a glacier, see?\NSpiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.36,1:04:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to people all the time.\NThat's like the sun coming down and melting the snow of the glacier.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.36,1:04:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A day, every day, a little of the glacier melts off and trickles down the side of the\Nmountain, and it keeps doing this.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.44,1:04:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what's holding up the glacier is getting weaker and weaker.\NWhat's left of the glacier, the sheer weight of it now, wasn't a problem before, but you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.48,1:04:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can see it's a pending disaster in the eyes of the world.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.24,1:04:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying it's my responsibility to teach people what I know, to also be prepared\Nin case spiritual reality moves much faster than what you would anticipate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.80,1:05:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt can just suddenly leave you in a different state.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.63,1:05:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And who's going to pay the bills now and empty the wastebasket?\NNobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.52,1:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why.\NYou pack up your dust.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.13,1:05:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You pack up your duds in the back of your truck and drive away.\NYou throw your tools in the back of the truck, and you drive to the other side of the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.24,1:05:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the end bite.\NNow people will say you've gone crazy, totally mad, and of course you have.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.52,1:05:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So divine madness can't overtake anyone, and also there's a stage in spiritual evolution\Nwhere you get the fire in the belly, where you play with the spirituality, you do courses,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.72,1:06:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you do workshops, and then all of a sudden it becomes like a fever of drivenness, that\Nthat is what now has priority over everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.51,1:06:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says to you, even me, yes, even you.\NThose decisions come about.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.68,1:06:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's not too uncommon.\NLet's say in 12 step groups.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.43,1:06:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not uncommon.\NThat's not uncommon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.81,1:06:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those step groups, you know, hey, hey, the relationship worked so long as he was drinking.\NShe was in charge.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.52,1:06:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,She ran the trick book.\NShe had the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.62,1:06:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the guy is sober, a different person.\NNow he's living by different rules on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.12,1:06:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He's talking about one day at a time as he does it, huh?\NAnd you can see how disruptions occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.52,1:06:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, that's why they have Al-Anon.\NSo we'll move to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.00,1:07:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just for the person who's stuck in the tree.\NYou can't see the trees and still can't see the forest.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.57,1:07:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to give them a sneaky way out.\NYou can stick with logic, reason, the Newtonian paradigm of causality, and still be spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.51,1:07:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And your sneaky out is quantum mechanics, aha.\NQuantum mechanics now introduces that something other than cause and effect and form is coming
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.75,1:07:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to play, and that's intention, the Heisenberg principle, as we say, everything comes into\Nmanifestation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.72,1:07:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result of intentionality or potentiality, it becoming an actuality when the conditions\Nare correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.61,1:08:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Heisenberg principle now is an advancement beyond the Newtonian paradigm because it introduces\Nthe enormous power of human consciousness and the will and volition, volition and will.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.66,1:08:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore.\NThe way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.30,1:08:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.\NThe way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.78,1:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The way.\NThe way.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.16,1:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So the way is that the potential collapses into the particle, which is the actual.\NAnd I see Henry Stapp has a new book out, which I haven't looked at or read yet, but
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.93,1:08:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to it.\NHenry Stapp, of course, has a website in which he explains this quite neatly, and this is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.79,1:08:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of an adaptation of it.\NSo you can still be logical, scientific, rational and not risk being looked at as weird and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.47,1:08:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual and yet see how phenomena that do not fit within the Newtonian paradigm.\Nparadigm can come into manifestation so we'll move to the next yes because now
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.73,1:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you're looking at somewhat different paradigms of reality the Newtonian is\Npredictable the nonlinear is not predictable it's more propositions and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.15,1:09:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihoods so you see likelihoods rather than certainties so it's a\Ndifferent dimension it's much more flexible the Newtonian paradigm is a box
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.29,1:09:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,very limited box the minute you open quantum mechanics now you open all kinds\Nof potentiality and variability so we'll move to the next one this is just to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.52,1:09:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate that the mind thinks dualistically and there's only one\Nquality now the calibrated levels of consciousness are just only a means of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.82,1:09:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,tracking the one quality the presence of truth to what degree it's like light or\Ndark so there aren't two options
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.20,1:09:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,opposites of true versus false hood there's only relative degrees such as\Nheat heat and cold are just manners of speaking they're not separate realities
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.60,1:10:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,heat is present to a variable degree truth is present to a variable degree\Nmove to the next the progressive fields of realization are interesting and I'm
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.69,1:10:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,writing about them lately because once you identify with the field instead of\Nthe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.99,1:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of the field, you now put yourself at the likelihood of identifying with the witness\Nrather than the participant.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.06,1:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you focus on the totality of experience from second to second, instead of the annoyances\Nof the particulars, then what you pick up is the energy of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.30,1:10:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't worry about the particulars because the field is going to see to it.\NIt's either all going to happen if the field is favorable, and it's not going to happen
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.62,1:11:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,if the field is not favorable.\NIn contemplation, then, instead of focusing on the specifics of content, you become aware
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.19,1:11:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the, you might say, the intuitive inference of the totality of the overall field.\NYou become one with the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.39,1:11:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,As you become one with the field, you move out of the movie.\NYou're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.43,1:11:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're now the witness of the movie, the observer-witness.\NSo instead of seeing yourself as the victim, because to be in the movie, you're always
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.55,1:11:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the victim of the movie, whether you have a good day or a bad day, depends on the vicissitudes\Nof the day.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.49,1:11:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't got any choice.\NWhen you move out of the movie, all is coming about of its own as the manifestation of that
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.39,1:11:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which it is.\NThen you've moved into the witness.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.18,1:11:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NAnd you're up above.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.53,1:12:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the movie.\NI am the movie.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.19,1:12:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you see, you know that because it registers, and you recognize the phenomena\Nout there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.49,1:12:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's being a participant as you become the field now, awareness, the observer, the witness.\NYou become the witness of it, and therefore, you don't necessarily have to have any comment
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.13,1:12:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NHere.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.38,1:12:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, just got blown up.\NSo, followed by a bomb and 30,000 people blown to bits.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.24,1:12:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You go, yeah?\NSo?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.46,1:12:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then what?\NAnd then what?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.46,1:12:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, so what?\NIt's been happening since the beginning of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.10,1:13:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is to excite you into a positionality so that you cling eagerly to the ego and don't\Nrealize that you're none of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.86,1:13:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you aren't a movie, then you're not a movie.\Nmovie, then of what interest is a movie? Once you realize that you are not a movie. If you think
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.73,1:13:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a movie, then every other movie is fascinating. Once you realize, oh, I'm not a movie?\NNo. What are you? You're the witness of the movie. You're the theater in which the movie is happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.94,1:13:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So to move into the contemplative position then, by supplication to God, you say,\Nto thee, O Lord, do I surrender my existence, that I may be thy servant. It's a supplication
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.98,1:14:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,asking not to get, but to be shown. It's more of a yin position. Contemplation is more yin.\NMeditation tends to be pretty yang, at least in its intention, it's very yang.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.38,1:14:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Very yang. Sit there cross-legged for six hours and don't scratch your nose.\NI'll hit you with a stick if you get looked stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.76,1:14:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And fall asleep. That's pretty yang. The inner phenomena, although ostensibly yin,\Nis better realized as a way of being that doesn't get isolated from daily life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.70,1:14:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you are. You're the supportive watcher, experiencer, and eventually\Nthe realization of reality as awareness itself. That even the watcher and the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.56,1:14:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,are delineation.\NWhy do the watcher and the witness have any capacity or value? It's because of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.32,1:15:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of awareness. Then you see, I'm not the subject of the movie. I'm not even the watcher or the\Nwitness. So you stop trying to delineate it, and you see what you are is a quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.99,1:15:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of awareness that is behind the observer-witness, which is the radiance of\Ndivinity which shines forth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.40,1:15:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of which arises all of creation.\NThank thee, we'll take a break. How long?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.25,1:15:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minute break, yeah.\NFirst thing to learn in spiritual work is discipline.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.12,1:16:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The lecture started five minutes ago, and all the crucial things have been said already.\NIt's a very special group of people. But don't think you're special just because you're special.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.78,1:16:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah, what I'm holding in mind is true. What I'm holding in mind is true over 90%, 92%, about 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.02,1:16:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so the question was, the only people that are attending a group like this are destined to become enlightened.\NIt says 90%.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.46,1:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because the Newtonian paradigm, you think you're being driven by the past. In reality, you're being pulled by the future.\NIf you're destined to become enlightened, you're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not. You're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.59,1:17:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Destiny wasn't to become enlightened, you wouldn't be here, nor would you be picking up the energy of the truth of it to carry forth into the world in subsequent generations, etc.\NTherefore, I said to be prepared, because those of you who have already chosen it, consciously or unconsciously, to become enlightened, will then pull yourself into that direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.76,1:17:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that could bring about changes in your life that can be surprising and quite a bit of a surprise.\Nrising, and quite maximum, quite maximum, maximum, yeah, then you know what maximum,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.27,1:18:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the word means, oh, that's what maximum means, yeah, like wiped out, outside we were just noticing,\Nthe world of causality, the world of the intellect, the world of cause and effect,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.24,1:18:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the world of the ego, sees life as going from imperfection to perfection, it's imperfect,\Nso you fix it, it's imperfect, so you paint it, embellish it, you put fur on it, or what,
