Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.40,1:23:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you got is why Mr. Asphalt is whispering to you the secrets, he's a reincarnation of the spirit\Nof the mystery schools, why are they a mystery, for Christ's sake, because you want to sell them,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.06,1:24:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you think, what is about truth that you want to mystify and keep secret, control,\Nright, control, all right, so in this lifetime, that comes back to you, and now you have a chance to say no to it,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.71,1:24:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,all right, so to know that everything is evolving automatically is a consequence of evolution,\Nbecause evolution is how creation is expressed to the witness, it isn't what it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.11,1:24:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's what it seems to the witness, and then when you let go of the witness,\Nyou are evolution, thanks, God, you are creation, man, what did you think it was,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.58,1:25:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you are the evolution of creation, you are the evolution of creation,\Nyou are how creation evolved itself, on up from the animal kingdom, on up through the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.60,1:25:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,dimensions, and then on into the non-linear, non-material presence, right, in that way,\Nthis returns to its source, so we'll resume the slides, you can't give a lecture without a slide,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.82,1:25:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,boy, give you a PhD, I say, where's your slides, you can't get a PhD without slides, nowadays it's\Nneat, you can give them all the slides in a little box like this, you know, used to be you had to have
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.28,1:25:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your slide box, so that the committee could review your work, you see, all right, these are the spiritual practices,\Nso by intention, by alignment, by supplication, and by declaration, the job for declaration,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.63,1:26:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the time to make sure who's going to pay your bills, who's going to carry out the garbage,\Nbecause by declaration, when you declare that you are a servant of Almighty God to thee, O Lord,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.98,1:26:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you have just changed everything, and don't be naive and think that you haven't, you have changed\Nit dramatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.22,1:26:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The sequence of a life events that you summon forth will unfold of a totally different dimension\Nthan people below 200, below 200, you go from imperfection to imperfection, to imperfection,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.32,1:26:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to imperfection, total dissatisfaction, resentment, pity, because you see whatever condition it is,\Nimperfection, you have desire and greed, desire and greed, I have to get it, so you go back to being a
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.72,1:26:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,protozoa,\Nprotozoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.60,1:26:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,protozoa,\Nprotozoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.74,1:27:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that only lives by getting,\Nand you're refuting the divinity of your creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.04,1:27:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which you are, by virtue of what it is, summons forth that which it needs from the universe,\Nit's hard to be poor, try it, it's hard to starve to death, try it, you can't starve to death,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.28,1:27:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,they call the police,\Nhe hasn't eaten in a week, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.93,1:27:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\NI was the consultant to the Episcopal Zen Monastery,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.12,1:27:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the sisterhoods and residents, Catholic, Episcopal, all that, you know,\Nand they'd bring in some monk from the Zen Monastery,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.82,1:27:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is he catatonic or is he in Samadhi?\NYeah, it needs his Tuesday,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.86,1:28:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is it Samadhi or Catatonia?\NThe observer can't tell,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.14,1:28:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if you've been there, you know,\Nthe way through,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.48,1:28:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but,\Nif you haven't been there,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.41,1:28:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you give him Thorazine and Shakti,\Nso in one of the books, anyway, I delineated how to differentiate,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.39,1:28:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course, with calibrated levels of consciousness,\Nyou can get right away with, is this a schizophrenic break,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.29,1:28:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or is this a guy in Samadhi, you know,\Nbecause it doesn't happen with such frequency,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.59,1:28:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and Catatonia is quite impressive,\Nand I'll tell you a story about Catatonia,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.64,1:28:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I was,\Nin the state hospital, right into the psychiatric hospital,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.15,1:28:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had a catatonic,\Ncatatonic, and he was a tall skinny thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.52,1:28:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wouldn't eat, so we tube fed him,\Nyou know, once a day, you got a tube down there,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.16,1:29:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but he would, in Catatonia, the person has,\Nwhat do they call it, cataplexy or something like that, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.86,1:29:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,if you put his arm like this, he will leave it there,\Nyou can come back three days from now, it's still there,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.82,1:29:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,immobile,\Nso we had a catatonic on the ward,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.82,1:29:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had the tube for these guys every morning,\Nmake sure the tube went down the esophagus and not the bronchi,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:23.52,1:29:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so, yeah, so the doctor had to come around and place the tube,\Nand then the nurse could take it from there,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.02,1:29:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but, so you don't get the enriched milk in their lung,\Nand kill them,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.01,1:29:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to feel sorry for these creatures,\Nbecause they didn't want to eat, they couldn't eat,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.98,1:29:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and tears would come to their eyes,\Nbut there wasn't anything I could do,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.34,1:29:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the law said you got to see to it they stay alive,\Nall right, so we had this catatonic,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.08,1:29:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and,\Nat the hospital, we had the doctor,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.74,1:29:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor was a short little guy with a bald,\Nand,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.04,1:30:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot his name now,\Nremember his name, yeah, anyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.54,1:30:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and anyway, we had a head nurse, just got off,\Nthe boat from Ireland,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.92,1:30:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and this was in Ward's Island, underneath the Chiropractic Bridge,\Nthe old Manhattan State Hospital,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.29,1:30:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and the personnel were mainly immigrants from Ireland, so,\Nyeah, Nellie Murphy, so Nellie Murphy was about 6'2",
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.63,1:30:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and all brawn,\Nand doctor, whatever his name is, I forget, it was about this high,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.54,1:30:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,well, the nurses weren't supposed to smoke or drink coffee in the nursing office,\Nand so this catatonic, you put them up against the wall,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.30,1:30:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and they tube feed them, and then you put them up against the wall,\Nand somebody just for something else to do,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.60,1:30:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,would put his hand like this, you know,\Nwell, you try and kid them out of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.99,1:30:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you go by, you put your hat on it,\Nyou salute it,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.89,1:30:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,pretend you're going to bite it,\Nno response,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.61,1:31:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,no response,\Nhe was this way for years.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:01.99,1:31:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, Nellie Murphy and Travis, that was it,\None day, Dr. Travis and Nellie,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:09.99,1:31:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,come walking down, because they were separate buildings,\Nit looked like Wuthering Heights or something, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.03,1:31:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,late 1800s, all these,\Nbrick buildings slightly tipped over the years,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.25,1:31:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and the floor is a little crooked,\Nand the smell of about 150 years of urine is coming up,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:28.75,1:31:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway, Nellie and Travis come walking down the walk, you know,\Nand this catatonic, it's sawed out the window,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.41,1:31:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,he hadn't spoken in 20 years,\Nand all of a sudden he says,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.32,1:31:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Travis and Murphy,\Nand the nurses quickly put away their cigarettes and coffee,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.24,1:31:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and opened the windows,\Nand he never said anything again.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.80,1:32:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we'll resume.\NSo how do you tell that condition from Samadhi, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.63,1:32:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the meditative states, you get into high states,\Nbut then when you open your eyes,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:12.60,1:32:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the state disappears,\Nor if it still maintains with eyes open,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.64,1:32:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it disappears when you begin to stand up and walk around,\Nand you can't participate in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.42,1:32:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so, because at a certain level,\Nthe capacity, actually, as the state evolves,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.32,1:32:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why I warned you about it,\Nyou hit a point in which,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.98,1:32:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to function is zero.\NThere isn't capacity to function.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.12,1:32:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, there isn't anybody to function,\Nnor is there anything to function about.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.67,1:32:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's hard to explain,\Nbut at 600, you become what's called a mystic,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.65,1:33:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world may have reasons for this body to go on walking around,\Nbut the body itself has no such interest, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.06,1:33:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, whatever happens is of karmic propensity,\Na karmic propensity,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.64,1:33:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nand if the karma is such,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.52,1:33:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then the continuation will continue,\Nand if the karma is already fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.68,1:33:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no obligation or commitment\Nbefore you have reentered this lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.62,1:33:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,then you may just topple over.\NSo, to refunction again requires
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.66,1:33:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the recreation of what you would call,\Nit's not recreated,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.87,1:33:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the activation of a potentiality,\Nit's not something called the personage.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:47.57,1:33:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a functionality,\Nit's not a thing or an entity.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.76,1:33:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the capacity to,\Nlet's say, explain to an audience what goes on,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.99,1:34:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,does so via a quality of the personage.\NSo, if the destiny is to continue on in the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.99,1:34:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say to teach for some reason,\Nteach or something,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.99,1:34:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then the capacity for personizing the knowingness,\Nemerges as vocabularization, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.23,1:34:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of which one is not the participant.\NThey have no idea what's going to be said next at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.86,1:34:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's great.\NNever heard it before.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.86,1:34:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there may or may not be\Nthe emergence of a person,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.70,1:34:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a personalization.\NIt's like an aspect of the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.12,1:34:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that by karmic control,\Nby contract almost,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.32,1:35:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by agreement,\Nit continues on to fulfill a function.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.32,1:35:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not the function,\Nnor is there any person to do the function.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:05.38,1:35:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The function is its own self.\NThe function functions
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.38,1:35:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,without any person behind the function,\Nwithout any purpose or direction,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.38,1:35:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's part of evolution.\NSo, those that are destined to become enlightened, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.77,1:35:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,express the potentiality\Nof creation and evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.15,1:35:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,returning to its source,\Nand that's what the world calls enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.15,1:35:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, enlightenment, at least from this realm.\NFrom other realms, it's called kindergarten.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.74,1:35:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,See, I'm a trainee for kindergarten.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.37,1:35:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These various spiritual practices.\NAll right, so once you've made the commitment,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.46,1:36:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason you made the commitment\Nwas because you're merely stating what you've already,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.46,1:36:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what your future is,\Nto become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.19,1:36:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody else is here.\NOnly golfers are at a class on how to golf,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.19,1:36:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I mean?\NWhy would you be in a class on golf?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.51,1:36:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, only because one has already chosen that\Nis, that is your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.51,1:36:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, one is,\Nthe appropriate way to be with that destiny
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.57,1:36:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of respect.\NRespect yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:38.89,1:36:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect the information.\NRespect the inspiration.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.89,1:36:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if that is your destiny,\Nthat certainly deserves respect.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.32,1:36:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect yourself.\NRespect truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.54,1:37:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't deviate it.\NTo not deviate out of guilt
Dialogue: 0,1:37:02.07,1:37:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is to just join the ego.\NNo, you don't deviate.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:06.07,1:37:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect truth out of your own integrity.\NTherefore, what is due a teacher?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.20,1:37:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Respect.\NThat's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.30,1:37:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not worship.\NNot glorification.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.83,1:37:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would the absolute truth\Nand the infinite glory of God
Dialogue: 0,1:37:23.50,1:37:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,need glorification\Nor amplification?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.50,1:37:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already so stunningly overwhelming what it is.\NAny two cents you can add is actually a detraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.33,1:37:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NOne of the things that are done then
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.77,1:37:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,to reinforce the commitment,\Nand I think they're quite interesting,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.86,1:37:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,just the sound, om,\Nwhich we're going to do this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.18,1:37:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,When do we do om?\NAfter lunch?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.25,1:37:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's morning now, right?\NWhen do we do om?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.70,1:38:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The chant?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.23,1:38:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This afternoon?\NOh, it's morning now.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.39,1:38:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, okay.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:07.58,1:38:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So we do om,\Nwhich we're going to do collectively.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.81,1:38:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the various variations.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.81,1:38:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Various variations of it.\NYou see that all these things
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.54,1:38:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,subserve spiritual intention.\NThis is over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.92,1:38:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These are over 200.\NThis is already 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.92,1:38:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to reach an advanced state\Nis to drink yourself to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.93,1:38:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,See if you can kill yourself with booze,\Nbad women and drugs,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.93,1:38:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,all at the same time\Nwhile you gamble away your last few dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:49.28,1:38:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And you either get to this way\Nor you leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.86,1:38:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nthrough that lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.68,1:38:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of people went out\Nfive or six times
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.68,1:39:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,due to addiction\Nand it's only the sixth lifetime
Dialogue: 0,1:39:02.68,1:39:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that they finally got sober.\NSo it ain't all that easy
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.68,1:39:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because that brings you right up at 540.\N540 is 0.4% of the human population.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.68,1:39:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,0.4% of the population\Never gets to 540.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.94,1:39:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't have to feel bad.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.48,1:39:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have to feel sorry\Nfor these people anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.48,1:39:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing is,\Nthey're way ahead of us already.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.86,1:39:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor elkies.\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.86,1:39:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540,\Nat 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.86,1:39:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,they're in a state\Nthat you wish you could experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.18,1:39:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo we,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.98,1:39:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the golden rule\Ndoesn't make any point below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.98,1:39:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said this morning.\NTo give a person an honest measure
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.72,1:39:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is stupid in certain cultures.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.72,1:39:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only over 200\Nthat it gains any validity.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.72,1:40:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the various things we do,\Nthe various prayers,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.42,1:40:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,walking the maze.\NWhen we were in Chartres Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.71,1:40:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they were very clever there.\NThey won't allow you to walk the maze.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.71,1:40:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They cleverly do that\Nby putting chairs all over
Dialogue: 0,1:40:10.71,1:40:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can't walk the maze.\NI guess they'd have
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.71,1:40:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,an endless parade of people\Nlined up outside
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.71,1:40:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,all walking the maze.\NI don't see what's wrong with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.06,1:40:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were in the cathedral,\NI'd have maze.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.16,1:40:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You go in there,\Nyou do the maze.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.16,1:40:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In,\Nout.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.16,1:40:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?\NExcept in the middle,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.58,1:40:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to go to the bathroom,\Nyou gotta,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.58,1:40:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.34,1:40:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have done it that way,\Nbut I don't know
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.34,1:40:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,their administrative problems.\NThey have a thing in the front for money.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:42.41,1:40:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They hit you with that right away.\NWalking in Chartres Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.02,1:40:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,money.\NThe next thing you get
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.50,1:40:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,is everybody's on their cell phone.\NHere's the most incredible.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.85,1:40:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrates over 700.\NI mean,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.17,1:40:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it's stupendous.\NYou can see that many workmen
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.17,1:41:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,gave an entire lifetime\Nsurrendering it to God
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.33,1:41:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as the perfection of their work,\Nthe Karma Yoga of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.68,1:41:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People are on their cell phones.\NIt's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.78,1:41:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're on their cell phones.\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:15.78,1:41:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.\NYou either get it
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.35,1:41:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or you don't get it,\Nyou know.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.18,1:41:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like seeing God\Nand saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.18,1:41:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,golly whiz, you know.\NThings become,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:31.63,1:41:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you see how 540\Nis the result of intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.24,1:41:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,By devotion and commitment to God\Ndoes the Ganges become holy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.42,1:41:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nmany of these things
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.42,1:41:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because they come\Nfrom different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.42,1:41:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of ridiculing them,\Nyou see that
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.42,1:41:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,turning a prayer wheel\Nby intention
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.94,1:41:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nlike genuflection,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.26,1:42:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,kneeling to pray,\Nput one's hands together like this
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.12,1:42:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is an act of respect.\NFor God,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.12,1:42:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,for a teacher,\Nfor truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.12,1:42:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for a divine place.\NPrayerful handcrafts,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.25,1:42:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,devotional acts,\Nturning the prayer wheel,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.25,1:42:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,burning of incense,\Nthe wailing wall,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.25,1:42:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,bathing in the Ganges,\Nthe prayer of St. Francis of Assisi.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.25,1:42:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a different level.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.25,1:42:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To be a channel of thy will,\Noh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.25,1:42:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the next.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.38,1:42:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is the left brain below 200.\NThis is the animal evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:42:43.23,1:42:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,up to consciousness level 200.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.55,1:42:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the animal evolution\Nup to consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.55,1:42:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's emotional primarily\Nand it has to do with survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.47,1:42:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with the core of the ego.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.57,1:43:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason ego\Nis the way he is
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.57,1:43:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is because he's programmed for survival.\NIf you want to take a piece of candy from him,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.88,1:43:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,he will bite you\Nbecause he's supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:15.03,1:43:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nwe respect the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.67,1:43:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than vilify it.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.77,1:43:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,my disagreement\Nwith the textbook
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.77,1:43:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Course in Miracles\Nis it seems to have a different energy
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.77,1:43:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,than the workbook\Nbecause it now gets into a dualistic positionality
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.66,1:43:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,about the ego.\NThe ego is innocent
Dialogue: 0,1:43:36.43,1:43:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of\Nthe fact that it's being
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.94,1:43:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what it was created to be.\NFor humans to be here,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.97,1:43:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution had to proceed up through the animal kingdom\Nto finally the development of a suitable
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.06,1:43:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,vehicle\Nfor higher consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:56.89,1:44:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For higher consciousness,\Nwhich we call human.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.21,1:44:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthe only reason we're here
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.72,1:44:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is because of our animal.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.36,1:44:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore,\Nwe're grateful for our animal
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.55,1:44:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say,\Nego baby,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.55,1:44:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,if it wasn't for you,\NI wouldn't be standing up
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.55,1:44:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,walking around\Nwithout the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.10,1:44:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't have a physicality\Nto walk around in.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.67,1:44:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this physicality reaches\Na certain point of evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.38,1:44:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but it has an even higher potentiality\Nthan just the animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.38,1:44:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 200,\Nthe energy of creation,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.22,1:44:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness,\Nthe light of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.22,1:44:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then,\Nmanifests
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.26,1:44:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin to experience\Nthe flow of the Kundalini energy
Dialogue: 0,1:44:44.26,1:44:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the brain switches\Nand processes information differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.26,1:44:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It experiences the world as more benign\Nand its intention is different.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.47,1:45:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the main reasons\Nis because at consciousness level 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.95,1:45:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you develop an etheric brain.\NThe etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.08,1:45:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The etheric brain.\NPrior to 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.59,1:45:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,people and animals\Ndon't have a personal karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.26,1:45:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they have a group karma.\NThey're controlled by an attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.26,1:45:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The attractor field draws all\Nlike unto like.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.36,1:45:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At 200,\Nyou now have choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.58,1:45:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You experience and realize\Nthat you are
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.80,1:45:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and this are is now responsible\Nand capable of choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.34,1:45:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Culpability also increases at 200.\NUnfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.34,1:45:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Also culpability.\NNow that you know that you are
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.27,1:45:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and others know that they are,\Nnow the consequences karmically
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.27,1:46:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,become different.\NThe karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.91,1:46:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of an animal eating a rabbit\Nis quite different
Dialogue: 0,1:46:06.91,1:46:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,than you're taking a human life,\Nlet's say.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.91,1:46:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo here karma changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.91,1:46:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The responsibility changes.\NYou have the inflow of Kundalini energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:16.91,1:46:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So we said below 200,\Nyour left brain linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.04,1:46:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,fight or flight,\Nalarm, resistance,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.04,1:46:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,exhaustion,\Nstress and the thymus,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.04,1:46:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,disruption of the acupuncture meridians,\Nmore prone to illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.04,1:46:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Neurotransmitter depletion\Nis one of serotonin.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.33,1:46:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOnce you switch the spheres,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.49,1:46:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you get a different dominance.\NIt's nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.49,1:46:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You're more interested in peace,\Npositive emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.49,1:46:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Immunity increases.\NHealing increases.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:47.10,1:46:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The acupuncture system is balanced.\NAnd the track to the emotions
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.06,1:46:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is slower than the prefrontal\Nand the etheric brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.06,1:47:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All this is crucial.\NAnd most of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.86,1:47:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know about it.\NSo we'll go to the next.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.95,1:47:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We go to the next.\NWe said that
Dialogue: 0,1:47:15.03,1:47:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's not a world of cause and effect,\Nit's a world of
Dialogue: 0,1:47:19.48,1:47:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you are\Ndraws like, draws to like.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.54,1:47:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you are by your own choice then.\NSo if we look at the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.58,1:47:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,correlated with the various phenomena\Nabout which sociologists are concerned,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.61,1:47:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, you don't see cause and effect.\NYou don't see cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.74,1:47:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You see concordance.\NI realized that,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.75,1:47:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember in World War II in the Navy.\NAfter paydays,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:52.04,1:47:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the same guys were always broke every Friday.\NSame guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.94,1:48:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Always broke.\NAnd I learned how to make money shooting craps.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:07.82,1:48:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you why you can't win at the casino.\NIf you look at the statistics,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:13.33,1:48:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if you look at shooting craps,\Nyou'll see that winning and losing,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.58,1:48:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,if you chart winning and losing in roulette,\Nor craps I think,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.58,1:48:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you see it spikes up,\Nthen it spikes down.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.58,1:48:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your winnings,\Nthese are your losses.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.58,1:48:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,These are your winnings,\Nthese are your losses.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.68,1:48:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How far of a loss can you take\Nbefore you're out of the game?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.13,1:48:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered that when I was 17.\NYou want to shoot craps? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.99,1:48:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How much you got on you?\NThree bucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.99,1:48:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I got ten.\NI'll go for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.54,1:48:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm going to get his three.\NIf I got ten.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.24,1:48:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:51.66,1:48:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the house,\Nthe house,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.66,1:48:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the house can go way, way down there.\NAnd you're going to get wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:59.07,1:49:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The house can afford, you know,\Nbeing five million behind.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.07,1:49:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:05.17,1:49:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just go on probability,\Nsooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:08.17,1:49:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a big wheeler,\Na big roller,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.17,1:49:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you got 40,000.\N40,000 is to a big house.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.71,1:49:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nthey eat that for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:17.71,1:49:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you go 100,000?\NCan you go 200,000?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.71,1:49:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have to send anybody even out\Nfor extra money
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.10,1:49:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you get well over a million.\NCan you go a million?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.10,1:49:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't go.\NSo you can see,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.10,1:49:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously,\Nit's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:34.10,1:49:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to get wiped out\Nby the downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.10,1:49:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NNever shoot craps
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.16,1:49:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you got a lot more money\Nthan the other guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.45,1:49:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you know why your ten of the legs are right.\NIt's because these guys here
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.86,1:49:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,always lose.\NThey always lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:56.41,1:50:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is practically zero.\NAnd criminality is an endemic way of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:02.41,1:50:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an endemic way of life, huh?\NThey receive it as criminal.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.92,1:50:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You practically never hear\Nof a child molestation,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.72,1:50:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,murder, kidnapping\Nas a single isolated crime.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.72,1:50:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't happen.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.58,1:50:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,it's fine.\NThe suspect has a record
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.58,1:50:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,going back to childhood.\NYou got 30 or 40 incidences
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.62,1:50:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of every kind.\NIt's a criminality is a way of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:28.90,1:50:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So this kind of an energy\Nwill pull prison to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.10,1:50:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I guarantee you\Nthey will be back in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.54,1:50:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Guaranteed.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.12,1:50:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By virtue of what they are.\NI guarantee you this person
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.24,1:50:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't going to be in prison,\Nyou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.46,1:50:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as a quality of that which they are.\NSo you pull to you
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.74,1:51:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the concept.\NIs the consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.74,1:51:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you are.\NThat which you are
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.74,1:51:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is destined for enlightenment.\NSo you pull to yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:51:07.74,1:51:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a lecture devoted to\Nhow does that happen
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.50,1:51:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and how do you do it and all.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.50,1:51:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you hear witnesses\Nthat you're all destined
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.14,1:51:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for such a destiny.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.72,1:51:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo people that are up here
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.72,1:51:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to pull to themself\Nthat which is,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.17,1:51:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you weren't destined\Nto climb Mount Everest,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.17,1:51:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be attending\Na course on mountain climbing.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.17,1:51:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.17,1:51:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see,\Nthis has nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.00,1:51:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with cause and effect.\NThese are movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.00,1:51:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go on from there.\N200 movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.26,1:51:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, these, we'll move on.\NThis is, we just,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.82,1:51:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we did represent this recently\Nat the World Children's Relief Fund
Dialogue: 0,1:51:57.82,1:52:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner in Phoenix\Nbecause people were devoted
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.89,1:52:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to helping\Nthe destitute.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:07.18,1:52:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the places\NI was interested in seeing
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.18,1:52:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,they were helping was Haiti.\NAnd we know in the Western Hemisphere,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.21,1:52:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move on.\NWe can move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.87,1:52:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Haiti,\Nthe only place in the Western Hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.45,1:52:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that's really very low\Nis Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.77,1:52:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And this group is very supportive\Nof building schools
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.63,1:52:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and life supportive systems\Nand raising the level of people in Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.59,1:52:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's a pretty benevolent project.
